mistral.full_ans: Yes, the Kingdom of Portugal had representatives in 1910. The Assembly of the Republic, established after the fall of the monarchy on October 5, 1910, consisted of members representing various electoral circles throughout Portugal, the Azores, and Madeira, as well as representatives for minorities. This assembly aimed to give voice to the people and ensure their representation in the governance of the kingdom.
